text: Voter advocacy groups in Georgia filed a lawsuit on Wednesday asking a federal court to force the state to restore nearly 200,000 people to its voter registration list ahead of the January runoff. The suit says the state had improperly removed the voters. https://t.co/eq0VLxrTVJ
